'''Apache ZooKeeper''' is a software project of the [[Apache Software Foundation]], providing an [[open source]] distributed configuration service,{{Clarify|date=March 2012}} synchronization service,{{Clarify|date=March 2012}} and naming registry {{Clarify|date=March 2012}} for large [[distributed systems]]. ZooKeeper was a sub project of [[Hadoop]] but is now a top-level project in its own right.
ZooKeeper's architecture supports [[High-availability cluster|high-availability]] through redundant services. The clients can thus ask another ZooKeeper master if the first fails to answer. ZooKeeper nodes store their data in a hierarchical name space, much like a file system or a [[trie]] datastructure. Clients can read and write from/to the nodes and in this way have a shared configuration service. Updates are totally ordered.<ref>{{cite web |url=https://cwiki.apache.org/confluence/display/ZOOKEEPER/ProjectDescription|title=Zookeeper Overview}}</ref>
ZooKeeper is used by companies including [[Rackspace]] and [[Yahoo!]]<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wiki.apache.org/hadoop/ZooKeeper/PoweredBy |title=ZooKeeper/Powered By}}</ref> as well as [[open source]] [[enterprise search]] systems like [[Solr]].<ref>{{cite web |url=http://wiki.apache.org/solr/SolrCloud|title=SolrCloud}}</ref>
==Typical use cases== * [[Name service|Naming service]] * [[Configuration management]] * [[Synchronization]] * [[Leader election]] * [[Message Queue]] * [[Notification system]]
